      "role": "user",
      "content": "So it's more of a recycling system than just waste being removed. You mentioned it's like a \"chaotic gathering\" that needs cleaning up—is there a way to describe the process of the hydrogen ions buildup and the subsequent \"buffering\" in a way that explains why it feels so disruptive to the muscle's function in the moment? Like, what's actually happening at the cellular level to cause that disruption?",
      "source": "evaluator"
